In the summer of 1991, a full 21 years after the unique fibreglass Mini was produced in Chile, another fibreglass-bodied Mini once again entered production. This time, it was manufactured in Venezuela and marketed under the rather charming name of Mini Cord. The producer, Facorca, harbored ambitious plans to sell the car throughout the Caribbean and Central America, and even had designs on establishing Brazilian assembly operations. A testament to the Mini's global appeal, even in its most unconventional forms.

